  "prefLabel": {
    "en": "Isoniazid Tablets",
    "ja": "イソニアジド錠"
  },
  "monographId": "JP18-isoniazid-tablets",
  "publisher": "JP",
  "status": "Official",
  "version": "18",
  "definition": {
    "en": "Isoniazid Tablets contain not less than 95.0z and not more than 105.0z of the labeled amount of iso-niazid (C6H7N3O: 137.14). Method of preparation Prepare as directed under Tablets, with Isoniazid. Identification Take a quantity of powdered Isoniazid Tablets, equivalent to 20 mg of Isoniazid, add 200 mL of water, shake well, and filter. To 5 mL of the filtrate add 1 mL of 0.1 mol/L hydrochloric acid TS and water to make 50 mL, and determine the absorption spectrum of this solution as directed under Ultraviolet-visible Spectrophotometry <2.24>: it exhibits a maximum between 264 nm and 268 nm. Uniformity of dosage units <6.02> Perform the test accord-ing to the following method: it meets the requirement of the Content uniformity test. To 1 tablet of Isoniazid Tablets add water to make exactly V mL so that each mL contains about 0."
  },
  "testSpecification": [
    {
      "@type": "IdentificationSpecification",
      "testName": {
        "en": "Identification"
      },
      "testType": "TestType-Identification",
      "testConditions": {
        "en": "Take a quantity of powdered Isoniazid Tablets, equivalent to 20 mg of Isoniazid, add 200 mL of water, shake well, and filter. To 5 mL of the filtrate add 1 mL of 0.1 mol/L hydrochloric acid TS and water to make 50 mL, and determine the absorption spectrum of this solution as directed under Ultraviolet-visible Spectrophotometry <2.24>: it exhibits a maximum between 264 nm and 268 nm. Uniformity of dosage units <6.02> Perform the test accord-ing to the following method: it meets the requirement of the Content uniformity test. To 1 tablet of Isoniazid Tablets add water to make exactly V mL so that each mL contains about 0.5 mg of isoniazid (C6H7N3O), and shake well to disintegrate. Filter this solu-tion, discard the first 10 mL of the filtrate, pipet 5 mL of the subsequent filtrate, add the mobile phase to make exactly 50 mL, and use this solution as the sample solution. Proceed as directed in the Assay. Amount (mg) of isoniazid (C6H7N3O) ＝ M S × QT/QS Amount (mg) of isoniazid (C6H7N3O) ＝ MS × AT/AS × V/100 MS: Amount (mg) of isoniazid for assay taken Internal standard solution—A solution of propyl parahy-droxybenzoate (1 in 4000). Operating conditions— Detector: An ultraviolet absorption photometer (wave- MS: Amount (mg) of isoniazid for assay taken Dissolution <6.10> When the test is performed at 50 revolu-tions per minute according to the Paddle method, using 900 mL of water as the dissolution medium, the dissolution rate in 20 minutes of Isoniazid Tablets is not less than 75z. ‌1202 Start the test with 1 tablet of Isoniazid Tablets, withdraw not less than 20 mL of the medium at the specified minute after starting the test, and filter through a membrane filter with a pore size of not more than 0.45 mm. Discard not less than 10 mL of the first filtrate, pipet 5 mL of the subsequent filtrate, add water to make exactly 50 mL, and use this solu-tion as the sample solution. Separately, weigh accurately about 0.1 g of isoniazid for assay, previously dried at 1059C for 2 hours, dissolve in water to make exactly 100 mL, then pipet 5 mL of this solution, add water to make exactly 50 mL, and then pipet 5 mL of this solution, add water to make exactly 50 mL, and use this solution as the standard solution. Determine the absorbances, AT and AS, of the sample solu-tion and standard solution at 267 nm as directed under Ultraviolet-visible Spectrophotometry <2.24>. Dissolution rate (z) with respect to the labeled amount of isoniazid (C6H7N3O) ＝ MS × AT/AS × 1/C × 90 MS: Amount (mg) of isoniazid for assay taken C: Labeled amount (mg) of isoniazid (C6H7N3O) in 1 tablet"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "AssaySpecification",
      "testName": {
        "en": "Assay"
      },
      "testType": "TestType-Assay",
      "testConditions": {
        "en": "Weigh accurately and powder not less than 20 Isoniazid Tablets. Weigh accurately a quantity of the pow- with 10 mL of the standard solution under the above operat-ing conditions, the relative standard deviation of the peak area of isoniazid is not more than 1.0z."
      }
    }
  ],
  "storageConditions": {
    "en": "Containers—Tight containers. Storage—Light-resistant."
  },
  "dosageForm": "Tablet"
